node.text:
Nothing like developing a ritual for saying goodbye that eases the thoughts that could cause separation anxiety in young kids. My parents used to drive us to Tennessee and just leave like thieves in the night while we were sleep to avoid the tears and hugs that could cause a dramatic departure. THAT SH*T WAS TRAUMATIC AS HELL FOR US!!!😠😡😤🤬 

So I choose to do it different. The kids are involved in the process and learn to cope with separation by telling us directly what concerns they have. Typically the fear of the unknown is what creates the anxiety, but when Dad says, “I will see you on this day…” no matter how long it is it eases their spirits— and the fear changes to an exciting countdown for when we get to be together again.💪🏾

Sidebar, notice Kay isn’t around in the beginning… It’s because goodbyes are hard for moms too. She slides in after the talks are all done and she knows her sons have been filled with confidence… Because the way them pregnancy hormones are set up, Kay liable to cancel the whole trip and ehbody will be sleeping in our bed next to her tonight.🤣🤣 DEAD ASS!🤨

#DevalesTrurh #TheEllises #JustDadding #RaisingKings #BuildAnEmpire #LeaveALegacy #MillennialParenting #MillennialMarriage

node.text:
Word to the wise fathers & fathers to be… If she falls asleep on the couch and you wake her up to go to bed, she will be mad… If she falls asleep on the couch and you leave her there to go to bed, she will be mad… Lastly, if she falls asleep on the couch and you wake her up to ask her what she wants to do… SHE WILL BE MAD!!!!🤷🏾‍♂️

Moral of the story, that pregnant couch sleep will be the best sleep of her life so don’t disturb her and let her sleep. Cause no matter what you do, she gonna wake up and realize that she pregnant and you not… AND SHE WILL BE MAD! So you might as well get some good sleep too because it’s easier to say, “Yeah you right baby…” on a good night’s rest.💪🏾 DEAD ASS! You’re Welcome!

node.text:
Yo real talk, I swear kids must be walking around the house turning on as many lights as they can as a TikTok challenge.😡 Yesterday I heard Jackson wake up, feet just touched the floor, he went and turned his room light on.🤯 IT WAS 9:26AM!!! DA F*CK YOU NEED TO TURN THE LIGHT ON FOR?!?!😠😡😤🤬 The Sunlight is what woke yo A** up!!!🤦🏾‍♂️

#DevalesTruth #TheEllises #JustDadding #MillennialParenting

node.text:
As a family we are competitive and supportive.💪🏾 From me to Kay all the way down to boys we will push each other to face fears and support each other through the process of seeing it through. That’s just the way we do sh*t!🤷🏾‍♂️ DEAD ASS!

node.text:
Nothing like developing a ritual for saying goodbye that eases the thoughts that could cause separation anxiety in young kids. My parents used to drive us to Tennessee and just leave like thieves in the night while we were sleep to avoid the tears and hugs that could cause a dramatic departure. THAT SH*T WAS TRAUMATIC AS HELL FOR US!!!😠😡😤🤬 

So I choose to do it different. The kids are involved in the process and learn to cope with separation by telling us directly what concerns they have. Typically the fear of the unknown is what creates the anxiety, but when Dad says, “I will see you on this day…” no matter how long it is it eases their spirits— and the fear changes to an exciting countdown for when we get to be together again.💪🏾

Sidebar, notice Kay isn’t around in the beginning… It’s because goodbyes are hard for moms too. She slides in after the talks are all done and she knows her sons have been filled with confidence… Because the way them pregnancy hormones are set up, Kay liable to cancel the whole trip and ehbody will be sleeping in our bed next to her tonight.🤣🤣 DEAD ASS!🤨

#DevalesTrurh #TheEllises #JustDadding #RaisingKings #BuildAnEmpire #LeaveALegacy #MillennialParenting #MillennialMarriage

Word to the wise fathers & fathers to be… If she falls asleep on the couch and you wake her up to go to bed, she will be mad… If she falls asleep on the couch and you leave her there to go to bed, she will be mad… Lastly, if she falls asleep on the couch and you wake her up to ask her what she wants to do… SHE WILL BE MAD!!!!🤷🏾‍♂️

Moral of the story, that pregnant couch sleep will be the best sleep of her life so don’t disturb her and let her sleep. Cause no matter what you do, she gonna wake up and realize that she pregnant and you not… AND SHE WILL BE MAD! So you might as well get some good sleep too because it’s easier to say, “Yeah you right baby…” on a good night’s rest.💪🏾 DEAD ASS! You’re Welcome!
